'''''Perittia andoi''''' is a [[moth]] of the [[Elachistidae]] family. It is found in [[Japan]] and the [[Russian Far East]].<ref>{{aut|Kaila, Lauri}}, 1995: A revision of the North American ''Perittia'' (= Onceroptila), with first nearctic records of the genus ''Mendesia'' (Elachistidae). ''Jounal of the Lepidopterists' Society'' '''49 (3)''': 208-222. Full article: [http://research.yale.edu/peabody/jls/pdfs/1990s/1995/1995-49(3)208-Kaila.pdf]</ref>

The length of the forewings is 6-6.5 mm.<ref>[http://www.jpmoth.org/Elachistidae/Perittia_andoi.html Japanese Moths]</ref>

